{
  "article_id": "Brantingham1993",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "What would you think if "
      },
      {
        "text": "the storied Lone Woman of San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " turned out to have been an Alaskan, not a "
      },
      {
        "text": "local Indian",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "?"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Ho, hum?"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Or anger at anyone having the nerve to challenge one of our most cherished legends?"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Marla Daily",
        "entity_key": "mda",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", chronicler of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", felt the savage whip of scientists a few years ago."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "That's because she ventured to suggest in an article in \""
      },
      {
        "text": "California History",
        "entity_key": "cahistory",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "\" that the Alaskan scenario should be explored."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "After she presented a paper to archeologists meeting at the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Museum of Natural History",
        "entity_key": "mu_museumofnaturalhistory",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " a few years ago, she got letters slamming her ideas as absurd."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"People were upset. I got a bunch of letters that this was an absurd hypothesis,\" she said."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"People don't want their bubbles to be burst."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"I'm not saying she is or isn't\" Alaskan, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Daily",
        "entity_key": "mda",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said, just that the question needs to be examined."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "After my recent Santa Barbara Yesterdays column, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Olivos",
        "entity_key": "ci_lo",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "history buff "
      },
      {
        "text": "Jim Norris",
        "entity_key": "jno",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " also questioned the origin of \""
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".\""
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "That was what "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Mission padres",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " named "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " after she was rescued in 1853 after an 18-year solitary sojourn on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the bleak island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "She was accidentally left behind when all other "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "were evacuated from "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in about 1835. \"No one says '"
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "' was "
      },
      {
        "text": "Chumash",
        "entity_key": "natam_Chumash",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " except a "
      },
      {
        "text": "Harrington",
        "entity_key": "jha",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " interviewee many years after the event.\" "
      },
      {
        "text": "Norris",
        "entity_key": "jno",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said "
      },
      {
        "text": "John P. Harrington",
        "entity_key": "jha",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was a noted local researcher into Chumash culture."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"I would suggest she was "
      },
      {
        "text": "Alaskan Indian",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " left with otter hunters around 1805-20,\" "
      },
      {
        "text": "Norris",
        "entity_key": "jno",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Norris",
        "entity_key": "jno",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Michael Redmon",
        "entity_key": "mred",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", librarian at the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Historical Society Museum",
        "entity_key": "sbhistoricalsoc",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", also questioned the authenticity of a commonly used photo of \""
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ",\" which appeared with my column."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Redmon",
        "entity_key": "mred",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said Southern California historians had raised questions about it. The woman pictured appears well-fed despite her many years subsisting on island fare, and younger than someone described as middle-aged."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Norris",
        "entity_key": "jno",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " is suspicious of it. \"Do we have any other "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " photos from 1853?\" he asked."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " died seven weeks after her rescue, apparently as a reaction to rich foods she was offered."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In her paper, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Daily",
        "entity_key": "mda",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz Island Foundation",
        "entity_key": "santacruzislandfoundation",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", raises some key points. First of all, residents of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", one of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "four southernmost channel islands",
        "entity_key": "i_southernchi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", were "
      },
      {
        "text": "Gabrielino Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Those of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the four northern ones",
        "entity_key": "i_northernchi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " were "
      },
      {
        "text": "Chumash",
        "entity_key": "natam_Chumash",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", she said."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "After being brought to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "chattered on in a language no local Indian could understand, according to accounts."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Emma Hardacre",
        "entity_key": "eha",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a Santa Barbaran who studied "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Lone Woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "legend years after Juana Maria's death, doubted that she was an island Indian, according to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Daily",
        "entity_key": "mda",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "She behaved like a woman \"who had knowledge of the amenities of life,\" ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Hardacre",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "eha",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said, not like someone raised on a barren island.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Then there were the dogs. When otter hunters "
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Charley Brown",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a German whose real name was "
      },
      {
        "text": "Carl Dittman",
        "entity_key": "cdi",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", rescued "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", they found wild dogs on "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\"They were about the size and form of a coyote, of a black and white color,\" "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said. \"I have seen the same kind of dogs among the Northwest Indians.\""
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " went back to shoot the dogs so he could run sheep there. "
      },
      {
        "text": "His son",
        "entity_key": "gnijr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "later reported that "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " told him they were \"of the Alaskan breed.\""
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "\""
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians from the north",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", particularly peoples from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Kodiak Island",
        "entity_key": "i_ko",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Aleutian Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_aleutian",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", participated in the California sea otter trade on and around "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " during the first part of the 19th century,\" "
      },
      {
        "text": "Daily",
        "entity_key": "mda",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria's story was fictionalized in the 1961 book by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Scott O'Dell",
        "entity_key": "sod",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", \"Island of the Blue Dolphins.\""
      }
    ]
  ]
}